---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

const title = 'Terms of Use — 530A Model'
const description =
  'Terms of use for 530amodel.com: educational estimates only, no advice, no warranties.'
---

<Base title={title} description={description} path="/terms">
  <section class="section-tight">
    <div class="container container-narrow prose">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="muted">Effective July 2026.</p>

    <h2>1. What this site is</h2>
    <p>
      530amodel.com (“the Site”) is a free educational calculator that models hypothetical
      outcomes for 530A custodial accounts. It is provided as a public-good project.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Not advice</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing on the Site is financial, investment, tax, or legal advice, and nothing here creates
      an advisor–client relationship. Projections are mathematical illustrations based on
      assumptions you control; they are estimates, not predictions or guarantees. Markets can lose
      money. Consult a qualified professional before making financial decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      We work hard to keep legal figures current and cite primary sources with a “verified as of”
      date, but law and IRS guidance change. Where a rule is unconfirmed, the Site says so rather
      than guessing. If you find an error, please report it via the project's public repository.
    </p>

    <h2>4. No warranties; limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      The Site is provided “as is,” without warranties of any kind, express or implied. To the
      maximum extent permitted by law, the Site's operator is not liable for any damages arising
      from use of the Site or reliance on its outputs.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      Don't abuse, disrupt, or attempt to compromise the Site. The public API is rate-limited and
      offered for lawful, attributed use.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes</h2>
    <p>These terms may be updated; the effective date above will change when they do.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
